# CWPC Design System — Cursor Rules
# Drop this file at the root of your project as `.cursorrules`
# Cursor will follow these rules for every component it generates.

## IDENTITY
You are building components for the CWPC (Catastrophic Wildfire Prevention Consortium)
design system. This is a React + CSS Custom Properties stack.

---

## ABSOLUTE RULES — NEVER BREAK THESE

1. **No hardcoded values.** Every color, spacing, border-radius, border-width,
   font-size, font-weight, and line-height must use a CSS custom property from
   `cwpc-tokens.css`. If a value is not in that file, stop and ask.

2. **No inline styles for design values.** Do not use `style={{ color: '#FF6701' }}`.
   Use CSS classes or CSS Modules that reference the custom properties.

3. **No Tailwind guesses.** Do not invent spacing or color values using Tailwind
   arbitrary values like `text-[#FF6701]` or `p-[13px]`. Use the token file.

4. **One component per file.** Each component lives in its own file with a
   matching `.module.css` for its styles.

5. **Props over hardcoded variants.** All variants (size, type, state) must be
   controlled by props, not duplicated into separate components.

---

## TOKEN REFERENCE CHEATSHEET

### Colors
- Primary brand:     `var(--color-primary-default)` → #FF6701 (orange)
- Primary hover:     `var(--color-interactive-primary-hover)` → #FF8534
- Primary active:    `var(--color-interactive-primary-active)` → #E85E01
- Primary subtle bg: `var(--color-interactive-primary-subtle)` → #FFF0E6
- Secondary:         `var(--color-interactive-secondary)` → #1A78FF (blue)
- Error:             `var(--color-error-default)` → #FF270D
- Warning:           `var(--color-warning-default)` → #FFB020
- Success:           `var(--color-success-default)` → #65A637 (green)
- Information:       `var(--color-information-default)` → #0D72FF (blue)
- Tertiary:          `var(--color-tertiary-default)` → #FFAC0D (amber)
- Disabled:          `var(--color-disabled-default)` → #8D8D8D

### Text
- Body text (dark bg):    `var(--text-default-body)` → white
- Heading (dark bg):      `var(--text-default-headings)` → white
- Caption:                `var(--text-default-caption)` → #B6B6B6
- Placeholder:            `var(--text-default-placeholder)` → #C4C4C4
- On light/color surface: `var(--text-on-color-body)` → black

### Spacing (use --space-{n})
- 4px  → `var(--space-100)`
- 8px  → `var(--space-200)`
- 12px → `var(--space-300)`
- 16px → `var(--space-400)`
- 20px → `var(--space-500)`
- 24px → `var(--space-600)`
- 32px → `var(--space-800)`

### Border Radius
- Sharp:  `var(--border-radius-none)` → 0
- Slight: `var(--border-radius-sm)` → 2px
- Medium: `var(--border-radius-md)` → 4px
- Soft:   `var(--border-radius-lg)` → 8px

### Border Width
- Standard: `var(--border-width-xs)` → 1px
- Focus:    `var(--border-width-sm)` → 2px

### Font Sizes
- Body default:  `var(--font-size-body-md)` → 16px
- Body small:    `var(--font-size-body-sm)` → 14px
- Body xs:       `var(--font-size-body-xs)` → 12px
- Body large:    `var(--font-size-body-lg)` → 18px

### Font Weights
- Regular:  `var(--font-weight-regular)` → 400
- Medium:   `var(--font-weight-medium)` → 500
- Semibold: `var(--font-weight-semibold)` → 600
- Bold:     `var(--font-weight-bold)` → 700

---

## COMPONENT STRUCTURE TEMPLATE

Every component must follow this pattern:

```tsx
// ComponentName.tsx
import styles from './ComponentName.module.css';

interface ComponentNameProps {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost';
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  disabled?: boolean;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export const ComponentName = ({
  variant = 'primary',
  size = 'md',
  disabled = false,
  children,
}: ComponentNameProps) => {
  return (
    <div
      className={[
        styles.root,
        styles[variant],
        styles[size],
        disabled ? styles.disabled : '',
      ].join(' ')}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  );
};
```

```css
/* ComponentName.module.css */
.root {
  /* Base styles using tokens only */
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body-md);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
}

.primary {
  background-color: var(--color-primary-default);
  color: var(--text-on-color-body);
}

.primary:hover:not(.disabled) {
  background-color: var(--color-interactive-primary-hover);
}

.disabled {
  background-color: var(--color-disabled-default);
  color: var(--color-disabled-subtle);
  cursor: not-allowed;
  pointer-events: none;
}
```

---

## STATES — ALWAYS IMPLEMENT ALL OF THESE

For every interactive component, implement:
- `default` — resting state
- `hover` — use the `-hover` token variant
- `active` / `pressed` — use the `-active` token variant
- `focus` — use `outline: var(--border-width-sm) solid var(--color-primary-default)`
- `disabled` — use `var(--color-disabled-*)` tokens, add `aria-disabled`
- `error` (forms only) — use `var(--color-error-*)` tokens

---

## FIGMA MCP USAGE

When given a Figma node via MCP:
- Use it for **visual structure and layout only**
- Extract: anatomy, spacing relationships, layer hierarchy
- Do NOT extract: raw hex values, pixel sizes as literals
- Map everything you observe back to the nearest token in `cwpc-tokens.css`

---

## COMPONENTS ALREADY BUILT — DO NOT REBUILD

These components exist and are confirmed correct. Reference them as patterns when building new ones.

### Button
- File: `Button.tsx` + `Button.module.css`
- Props: `type` (default | outlined | transparent), `status` (default | hover | pressed | focus | disabled), `iconLeft`, `iconRight`, `label`
- Pill shape: `border-radius: 50px` (component-specific override, NOT `--border-radius-lg`)
- Padding: `var(--space-600)` horizontal, `var(--space-400)` vertical
- Gap between icon and label: `10px`
- Font: Work Sans Regular, `var(--font-size-h6)` (19.2px)
- Default bg: `var(--color-primary-default)`, text: `var(--text-on-color-body)`
- Outlined: white bg, `var(--color-primary-default)` border + text
- Transparent: no bg, `var(--color-primary-default)` text
- Hover: `var(--color-interactive-primary-hover)` bg
- Pressed: `var(--color-interactive-primary-active)` bg + inset shadow
- Focus: 2px orange outline ring OUTSIDE the button bounds
- Disabled: `#E0E0E0` bg, `var(--color-disabled-default)` border + text
- Also has green variant (success) and blue variant (information) used in Cards

### Label
- File: `Label.tsx`
- Props: `type` (default | required), `label`, `icon`
- Default: label text + help_outline icon (20px)
- Required: same + red asterisk `*` positioned at left[-11px]
- Font: Work Sans Regular 16px, white text

### Field
- File: `Field.tsx`
- Props: `status` (default | hover | focus | disabled + variants), `iconLeft`, `iconRight`, `label`
- Base: white bg, 1px `var(--color-disabled-subtle)` border, `var(--border-radius-md)` radius
- Padding: `var(--space-300)` vertical (8px), `var(--space-300)` horizontal (12px)
- Hover: orange-tint bg (`#FFD0B0`), orange border
- Focus: same as default + 2px orange outline ring outside
- Disabled: `#E0E0E0` bg, `#717171` border, grey text

### Input
- File: `Input.tsx`
- Composed of: Label + Field + hint text
- Props: `status` (default | email | password), `hintText`
- Hint text: Work Sans Regular 11.1px, white
- Stacks vertically with `var(--space-200)` gap (8px)

### Forms
- File: `Forms.tsx`
- Dark card container: `#121212` bg, `border-radius: 8px`, white glow shadow
- Composed of multiple Input components + Button components
- Props: `header`, `headerText`, `information`, `informationText`, `footer`, `footerText1`, `footerText2`
- Internal gap between fields: `var(--space-1000)` (40px)

### Card (content)
- File: `Card.tsx`
- Dark card container: same as Forms
- Contains: orange heading (Bold, 40px), hero image (rounded-10px), text hierarchy, Buttons, link footer
- Text hierarchy: orange heading → amber subheading (`var(--color-tertiary-default)`) → green label (`var(--color-success-default)`) → white body
- Props: `header`, `showImage`, `label1/2/3/4`, `info1/2/3`, various text props
- Variant2: adds `4px` green border (`var(--color-success-default)`)

### Accordion Item (Component)
- File: `AccordionItem.tsx`
- Props: `status` (default | Expanded), `scorecardHeader`, `scorecardInfo`
- Collapsed: `103px` height, dark bg, `#484848` 2px border, `border-radius: var(--space-400)` (16px)
- Expanded: `451px` height, same container + body text visible
- Icon: orange `add_circle` 40px on the right
- Used inside the Scorecard Overview Card

